ram charan (hindi: राम चरण)( february 24, 1720 - 1799 ad) or ( māgh shukla 14, 1776 - vaisakha krishna 5,1855 bikram samwat) is the founder of a unique religious tradition in india called ram snehi sampradaya. he initiated,illustrated and preferred the nirguna (absolute) bhakti, although he was not against saguna bhakti. he initiated and tried to eliminate "show", blind faith, hypocrisy and misled existing in the hindu religion and preferred to worship 'name of god' that is "rama" over god, to not get involved in false "show" activities.